snippet: Lawmakers voted to ensure that the United States could impose duties on subsidized goods from China and Vietnam.
abstract: Lawmakers vote to ensure that the United States could impose duties on subsidized goods from China and Vietnam, overwhelmingly rejecting a conservative group's attempt to portray it as a tax increase; bill, which the House passed 370 to 39, is expected to be signed into law by Pres Obama.
lead_paragraph: Lawmakers voted to ensure that the United States could impose duties on subsidized goods from China and Vietnam.

headline.seo: House Approves Bill That Would Impose Duties on Imported Goods
headline.main: House Passes Bill to Address China Subsidy
headline.print_headline: House Passes Bill to Address China Subsidy
